During the Spring Festival, fewer and fewer street stalls sell gift boxes for relatives. Only a few stall owners wear masks. One stall owner said: "This year to buy less, less people on the road. " After saying, he tightened his nose mask subconsciously.

The full text is 3,623 words and takes about 7 minutes to read

In Gucheng County, Hebei Province, 900 km from Wuhan, it is clear that the 2020 Spring Festival will be a busy time for leaders from the county level to the villages and towns.

On January 27, the third day of the Lunar New Year, the county Party secretary visited the newly-built isolation ward. County Health Commission no longer holiday, set up a special prevention and control office to deal with the epidemic.

Fever clinics have been set up in local county hospitals, but there are still fever patients who do not wear masks. During the Spring Festival, there are almost no visits to relatives and friends in the area. Telephone calls have become the mainstream. There are few pedestrians on the streets. People are taking the epidemic seriously and staying indoors.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
On January 25, medical staff of the county hospital were spraying disinfectant on the curtain of the clinic building. Photo by Han Ruxue, Beijing News



Official: Local Quarantine Ward opened, county Party secretary visited

Gucheng County is located in the southeastern part of Hebei Province, bordering Shandong Province, 900 kilometers away from the outbreak center in Wuhan. Depending on the well-developed traffic network, the Spring Festival tide in and out of the migrant workers come and go.

A battle against the plague was waged in this small town.

During the Spring Festival, an isolation ward was completed in Gucheng County. The isolation ward is located in the Yingdong Development Zone on the edge of the county town. It was originally a branch of the county hospital and was intended to be a medical and health center. On January 26, more than a dozen workers were busy inside the isolation ward. Staff said that the ward was originally prepared according to the hospital, has not started operation, is still in the construction phase, is expected to be completed the same night.

On January 25, the county magistrate came to the construction site of Yingdong isolation ward, to the county hospital put forward the "Long-term war preparation, the implementation of prevention and control of material reserves" requirements. January 27, the county Party secretary to Ying-dong Isolation Ward Inspection Guidance.

Throughout the Spring Festival, the county health commission did not rest, set up a special prevention and control office, statistics reported in the area of Wuhan returnees, fever patients and other related epidemic data.

Epidemic Prevention and control from top to bottom, in January 25, the first day of the first month before the implementation of grass-roots. Every township and village has carried out related propaganda through the broadcast form, many villages and towns set up the barrier at the key junction "closed village" , does not allow outsiders to enter.

County in a large-scale nursing home, usually there are about 50 old people, during the New Year there are more than a dozen old people left in the nursing home. New Year's Eve also allows family members to visit, to the first day of the strict prevention and control of the epidemic, do not allow outsiders to enter.

A number of local pharmacies, have a shortage of masks and price increases. A large pharmacy staff said the store's stock of one-off masks on the 23rd has been out of stock, upstream business is located in Hengshui, a wholesaler, there are also out of stock. Another chain pharmacy staff said that on the 26th, just into a batch of masks, currently only with a filter cotton mask, also sold 16 yuan a morning, 8 pm has risen to 18 yuan a, "tomorrow more expensive, to sell more than 20 Yuan A. "

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
January 25, the county hospital at the door, the eye-catching location marked with fever clinic location and route. Photo by Han Ruxue, Beijing News

Hospital: Disposable Masks for most medical and protective equipment

January 25, the first day of the Lunar New Year, is also the second day of the first-level response in Hebei Province. At the entrance of the county hospital, there is a sign that says, "please send fever patients to the fever clinic. ". This hospital is a second-class a hospital, but also the county and even the city's only a national Baijia hospital.

Many of the doctors on duty in this hospital during the Spring Festival were temporarily transferred to other shifts because of the epidemic. For them, the disposable mask is still the most people can get protective equipment, a little better, is to wear two layers.

A doctor in the emergency department said there were not enough masks for doctors and nurses. When patients with fever, they would be given masks, but they were not professional masks, just ordinary disposable masks. The hospital, including billing, drug distribution and other multi-room doctors wear only one-time masks, some doctors will wear two masks. "there is no professional mask, " said one doctor

At present, doctors in charge of body temperature measurement wear surgical masks; doctors in fever clinics and inhalation medicine wear N95 masks, and doctors in other departments wear ordinary disposable masks, according to doctors at the hospital's triage desk.

Li Li Zhao is on call at the fever clinic, as she performs the first procedure on a feverish patient -- taking her temperature. Wearing goggles and a surgical mask, she said, they have an eight hour shift, with staff on duty 24 hours a day at the fever clinic, and there is no time to spare. Doctors in fever clinics wear surgical masks and goggles. In view of this epidemic situation, has built the isolation ward, if the diagnosis then sends to the city's designated hospital.

For patients who come to take their temperature, Zhao will ask for names, addresses and contact information. She will also ask if they have returned from other places, if there are any people from other places in their families, and if there are any family members from Wuhan. Like the clinic where Zhao Lili is, the hospital has two, north and south two clinic buildings each one, responsible for doctors in front of a thick registration book.

There are three doctors in the emergency department. About two o'clock in the afternoon, there are four or five patients in the room, all have cough, headache and other symptoms. The three emergency room doctors wore masks, no goggles or protective clothing, and said they wore ordinary disposable masks. One wore two layers. There are a few people to see a doctor do not wear a mask, occasionally heard others cough, subconsciously covered his mouth.

A medical professional said that the COVID-19 pneumonia has the latent period may transmit the virus, and there are some infected people who do not have symptoms of fever, in this case, doctors treating patients with suspected discomfort should wear protective clothing, N95 masks and goggles and other professional protective equipment.

At the county hospital, people with uncomfortable symptoms who may have new-type pneumonia can have blood tests and lung CT scans, "but they are not targeted, " the emergency physician said. The hospital has no test for the new type of pneumonia, and suspected cases are sent to designated hospitals in the city, where the doctor recommends home monitoring for patients who do not have a fever.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
January 25, the first afternoon of the New Year, the county hospital emergency room because of a cough, cold to see patients, some patients do not wear a mask, heard the sound of coughing covered mouth. Photo by Han Ruxue, Beijing News

Public: part of the health care providers lack awareness of protection

Under the epidemic situation, it is very important whether the patients who come to the hospital have the consciousness of protection.

The Respiratory Department of the county hospital is on the first floor and ends in an isolation ward. On January 25, a reporter from the Beijing News observed that there were several beds in a ward of the Department of aspiration medicine, and the temperature was obviously several degrees higher than outside. The old man in bed coughed and was accompanied by a dozen people, either sitting or standing, no one wearing a mask.

On the fourth floor, the Children's ward, where children's cries and coughs are heard, there are almost no face masks, from adults to children.

The 77-year-old grandmother, who lives in Xibantun village, Xibantun town, Gucheng County, visited the fever clinic of the county hospital on the afternoon of January 25. Her body temperature was 37.2 C. The doctor advised her to have a blood routine examination and a lung CT examination, but she refused on the grounds that, these tests cost hundreds of dollars to do, and you have to be hospitalized to be reimbursed, or you have to pay for them yourself.

Sun said her husband was in the county hospital and she had to take care of him in the ward, which was why she had come. After seeing the fever clinic, her hands more than two boxes, one box is used for pain, antipyretic ibuprofen tablets; the other box is run lung phlegm, cough Dingchuan Lugen Loquat Leaf particles.

Grandma Sun didn't know if anyone from Wuhan was in the village. Her 18-year-old grandson, who is studying in a neighbouring province, knew about the outbreak but felt "fine" . Grandma was the only one wearing a mask. The pink one was given to her by the fever clinic doctor. She wore it upside down, but she didn't know it.

Many ordinary residents are even less aware of protection. Although the only cinema in the county is closed. But in a clearing not far from the cinema, eight or nine elderly people sat around playing cards and asked for information about the outbreak. They knew the general situation, but they still did not wear masks and played cards together.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
On January 25, a notice was put up at a cinema in the county seat, which has been closed since the early 1930s because of a new type of pneumonia. The opening time is yet to be determined. Photo by Han Ruxue, Beijing News

GENERATION: Difference of epidemic prevention consciousness between young people and old people

Lin Qing, 26, who works in Beijing, had his first brush with his father about the outbreak in a shopping mall on January 22, the 28th of the 12th month. Lin Qing, who works in Beijing, had just returned to his hometown and was shopping with his parents for New Year's Eve.

Lin Qing insisted that the family wear masks when they go out to the mall, which she bought in Beijing. Lin Qing's father made a mountain out of a molehill for fear of being recognized as a "disgrace. " . Half an hour into the father daughter battle, Lin Qing declared victory. When we got to the mall, there were very few people wearing masks.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
On January 25, the afternoon of the first day of the Lunar New Year, 89 old people were playing poker in a vacant lot near a residential area in the county seat. None of them wore masks. Photo by Han Ruxue, Beijing News

There is no exact time when the news of the epidemic will spread in the small town. On January 24th, on the eve of the Lunar New Year, during the reunion dinner, Lin Qing again asked not to go to relatives'houses or drop by. The 70-year-old grandfather was the first to object: "Even if there is a virus, but how can we say, relatives think of our family, unless the government issued documents. "

Lin Qing's cell phone opened up a group of classmates, similar contradictions in almost everyone, living in the small county elders, there is no more access to information about the epidemic, and the corresponding lack of awareness of protection.

The turning point came in the early morning hours of January 25, the first day of the lunar new year, when Lin Qing's county towns and villages broadcast over loudspeakers, asking everyone not to go to their homes to pay New Year's greetings and not to visit relatives or friends.

A government official said that the leaders of the 30 counties met until 10 o'clock at midnight in 2008 to speed up the propaganda work in accordance with the requirements of the provincial and municipal levels. That night after the meeting, the township level again to work deployment meeting, the next morning, the implementation of each village, notice villagers no longer go door-to-door New Year.

The village reacted quickly to the clear instructions. A number of villages through pulling banners, digging ditches, piles of soil, set up a special person to guard the intersection, and other ways to discourage relatives New Year. For rural areas, where medical resources are relatively scarce, isolation is a viable option.

The conflict between the younger generation and the older generation is gradually easing up. During the Spring Festival, the Lin Qing family finally agreed to call relatives and stop moving around.

(at the request of the interviewee, Zhao Lili, Li Meng and Lin Qing were given pseudonyms.)
